<m0>   KINGSTON, Jamaica (--) (AP) (--) In an effort to develop a new generation of better-educated citizens and improve living conditions in Jamaica, Prime Minister P.J. Patterson has announced increased allotments for social departments in the 1996-97 budget.<ep>
   Among the highlights of Patterson's $2.5 billion fiscal budget are a $272 million investment in education and training and new $4.2 million inner-city development program to improve sanitation in downtown Kingston.<ep>
   Patterson also announced the creation of a Social Investment Fund, which allows communities to access up to $40,000 to improve their environment.<ql>
